I hear lots of people constantly talking about the #entrepreneur path... "The journey"... apparently everyone is an expert 🤷🏻‍♂️

Here is the reality 👉 you won't know your path until you try, and more importantly you won't ever get "there" if your not extremley disciplined & dedicated --- not just motivated. 

I made tons of mistakes on this path. More decisions than I can think of, that I could have done differently.
But we did it. We came this far and never quit.

@frank_vmisports and I hit what seemed like insurmountable obstacles, but you eventually realize, they are just road blocks to go through. 
 
Invariably everyone at some point says "I want to do X"

Cool. Show me. Go for it. Get up EVERY SINGLE DAY and do whatever your "X" is, NO MATTER WHAT.

Then you won't need any motivational speaker to tell you about "the path" or "the journey"

You'll be living it.... Or, you won't.... Your call.

Shoutout to all the real ones out there putting the work in, we 👀 you. 

#vmisports #visionmeetsinnovation

Everybody wants the “Hack”… just hear me out…

The truth is there isn’t any one hack to be successful or ever be great at what you do… I’m speaking from experience.

The goal post should be to HELP PEOPLE & PROVIDE VALUE. 

Then you have to have a process that works towards that goal.

Today I got pretty amped up talking to  the 1️⃣ and ONLY @craigsiegel_cls 

Not only is Craig a part of the @vmisports family, but he is a very successful host of the #clsexperience 🎙️ podcast. 

Today was the first time we sat down in person — now for context, I had already had an owners meeting with @frank_vmisports followed immediately by a long production meeting with our whole team here in NY — and then another meeting with our Marketing team. 

Immediately I sat down with Craig afterwards, and within 5 minutes he told me I was giving off great energy & passion. He asked me if this is how I always am… (remember we’ve never met)

I told him exactly what I tell everyone we get a chance to meet or work with — this is who I am, I want to help people, not just in our building but every partner and customer we have. Anyone we can service in their journey for health. 

My passion to help others is what drives me every day. It drives what we do here @vmisports 

If we can help you, let us know. 

2023 🚀🚀🚀

📸 shooter: @joeycamarda

One things is for sure, in business and in life.. you’re going to to shovel some shit.

You’re going to have to show up, consistently, if you ever want to really get anywhere special.

You can’t fake it ‘til you make it. You can’t phone it in. You just can’t. It doesn’t work and you can never go back in time to do it over.

Truth be told, talent doesn’t always equate to success, and “who you know” only gets you in the door. 

You have a responsibility to yourself & to everyone that supports you and believes in you, to show up and make shit happen.

I’ve been in the same business for almost 20 years and I’m just really getting warmed up 💪

You can’t bullshit me. You won’t outwork me. And it’ll probably take a Mack Truck to stop me 🤷🏻‍♂️ 

Find your passion, your reason, your “why”, and ignore all the people that have an opinion, or doubt you, etc. 

I want to help people improve their physical performance and health, in part through supplementation @vmisports 

And I’m hoping some people check out our podcast 🎙️ @thevisioncast and that our messages are helpful to them 👊

This is a short crappy clip doing light weight from a few months ago. It means nothing.. and yet it means everything. 

6-7 years ago, I was burnt out. I was sloppy. I forgot what got me there. I was comfortable being nothing.

Took me over a decade to get back to training how I was used to. 

Took me even longer to realize that I should be doing it for me, not for an exterior purpose or goal. 

If I am not healthy and slinging some plates, I am no good to anyone.. not my family, not my team & not our customers. I had to get back on my game.

The differnce for me was I got comfortable being overweight sitting in meetings and on planes and at a desk.  STAY OUT OF YOUR COMFORT ZONE.

I got sloppy. I let the business take away my health. 

All while I was trying to help people be healthier?! 

I’m on a fucking mission right now — if you want help, or need advice from our team, hit us up @vmisports 

We are going to light shit up this year, you can count on it. 

#vmisports #seeyouontop #visionmeetsinnovation

Surround yourself with people who support your goals and vision, and whom you support theirs.

2022 was our single biggest year ever. 

2023 is already on pace to beat that by a long shot.

The Goal is to Provide Value…that’s “winning”

Over 18 years ago I started in retail at #GNC as many of us did.  I quickly realized I could help every customer that walked in, potentially improve their health & fitness. 

But it was too small. Not enough impact.

So a few years later I went into distribution at #UNFI & then later, #LoneStarDistribution and I saw I could impact hundreds of retailers at wholesale, who were in turn selling thousands of products, to millions of people. 

But it was too small, not enough impact.

So in 2012 I pitched the idea that is now @vmisports to my soon to be business partners, including @frank_vmisports 

2013 ➡️ @vmisports first product is born, along with my mission to help more people on a broader scale.

There were challenges at first… 

I had a full time job when we launched.. this was tough
I allowed others to influence formulas and creative.. this was a mistake
The idea of branding escaped me.. I didn’t know what I didn’t know 🤷🏻‍♂️

But despite these & many other obstacles, it’s taken 10 years, and now we’re hammering away every day to develop & produce the best products we possibly can, with some of the best tasting flavors we can source 😉 

Now we can have unlimited positive impact 👊

Why do I say all this? 

Because despite the length and challenge of the journey, THE GOAL IS TO PROVIDE VALUE.

We @vmisports are 💯 in the business of making great products that solve a problem/serve a need for consumers. 

ProtoLyte👉 whey protein w/ hydration & digestion
KXR👉 extreme pre workout w/out the crash
HEAT Carnitine 👉 stim free weight loss support

For me, I’m lucky enough to be a part of an industry I am passionate about. But I have to constantly focus on making sure we provide value in all areas.

I challenge & encourage you to focus on doing the same — and you will reap the rewards of helping others. 

Go after it, and never give up. #SeeYouOnTop

Sometimes life takes a turn you don’t even see coming.

I was lucky it took a turn for me when I got to college. 

I missed an opportunity to play college baseball, and it turned out to be one of the best redirects you could hope for.

20 years later, I’ve spent a career channeling my passion & energy into helping others in their health & fitness journey.

And as @proctorgallagher would say, you must willingly give & graciously receive.  I try to give my time and experience to those who ask & need it.

And if you’re not willing to do (give) more than what you are being paid, you will never be paid for more than you do. (Paraphrasing Bob here @proctorgallagher )

I believe this to be true. Bob also reminds us, if you have to think before you give, you’re trading, not giving.

And listen — as a business owner, I am not saying your goods & services should be free... I am saying you can give / give back to people and community & it will be it’s own reward. 

People who’ve know me the longest used to hear me say “nothing is ever free..” 

That’s not entirely true. But you must be willing to give, and graciously receive when it comes back around.

My ✌️ 🪙 for today. #peoplehelpingpeople

Standards Matter. 

Especially when we’re talking about buying products you ingest. 

In the world of social media advertising, it’s hard for consumers to tell what’s really a good product/brand, and what’s not… I get it.

Simply because there is too much external loosely affiliated influence, and a ton of bad information.

Make sure you do your research. Make sure you know what you’re buying, and WHY you are buying “that one”

There are a lot of great brands out there — but there is a-lot of shit too.

Don’t buy the shit. Just don’t. 

And that doesn’t mean don’t buy from a Facebook ad or even an influencer — it means, make sure no matter what, you know what you’re buying is the quality you’re looking for — have a standard.

Time. It just takes time.  Longer than most think it does. Longer than I ever thought, for sure. 

The clock humbles us all. It never stops, ever. 

But of course, that’s why most people don’t do certain things, even if they would like too.

They aren’t willing to sprint when the distance is unknown. 

They prefer short term comfort — and the illusion that they are doing ‘everything possible’ to achieve their goals. 

Most people are in fact just lying to themselves.

Most days when I get up and feel like a failure, because we aren’t where we want to be yet. 

More nights than not, when I go to bed, I feel like a poser, because I didn’t work harder that day. 

Every time someone asks me what I do for a living, I feel a sense of embarrassment, because I think to myself, we haven’t really accomplished anything special yet. 

I’m not sure I’ll ever get out of that headset, despite my efforts (and reading several mindset books) 

I’m also not sure it’s a bad thing. Maybe that’s the motivation. Maybe the fear of never accomplishing more is what keeps me moving foward.

I know I have a long way to go. And you might too..
But keep working, keep grinding. The results you’re looking far might be closer than that appear. 

2024’s looking bright, just keep your foot on the gas 👊
